records.addlTxt:
On count 1, the defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of eight (8) years.  That is three (3) years initial confinement followed by five (5) years extended supervision..
On count 5, the defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of six (6) years.  That is three (3) years initial confinement followed by three (3) years extended supervision, concurrent with count 1.
The Court finds the defendant not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.
The Court orders that restitution be paid at the rate of 25% of the prison wages and work release funds.  The balance remaining at release from prison to be paid as a condition of extended supervision at a rate to be determined by the supervising agent.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Pay court costs;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) defendant must register as a sexual offender and comply with all terms of the Sex Offender Registry;
4) defendant is not to possess or use any device capable of connecting to internet unless approved by the agent;
5) have no contact with the victim, M.E.G. or her family;
6) have no contact with anyone under the age of 18 unless approved by the agent;
7) maintain absolute sobriety;
8) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
9) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
10) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
11) AODA assessment and follow through;
12) Pay restitution of $1,900.00 to the victim.  (The parties have 60 days to submit a stipulation regarding additional restitution for lost wages.  If not stipulation, the matter will be set for a hearing.)
The defendant has credit for 2 days.
Minutes.
